        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> While I would like to see DoT stacking, it is very limited in its overall impact.  Most necros will not see any affect from it.  DoT stacking is purely designed for the high end raiding necros.  Thus, the elite.  I am not part of that and may never be.  But I do not see how DoT stacking will balance the class.  All it will do is make necros more frienly for end game raiding and some groups.</P><P>   I am sure VI is scratching its head on why a primarily solo class is asking for a change that will only benefit it in non-solo situations.  Of course, I know you will say:  "Hey, VI has been purposely gearing to groups and slowly making soloing at high levels unattractive.  Additionally, you cannot get the better dropped stuff soloing."  These are valid points.  But do not detract from the fact that the DoT stacking is only really beneficial for high levels.  Yes, low levels concievably could do it too.  The reality is it will be unlikely to spark a sudden rush to play low level neccros just so you can DoT stack with each other.</P><P>   Just a thought.  There are good arguments against this view, but I think it needs to be said again here.</P><P>52nd Heretic of Misty Knight (Tholluxe Paels)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
