        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Nr 4: Add 1k Hp to 59 pet and up damage to 65 max hitt.(For partys)<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote>As a <i>Magician</i> I would have to say, <i>Be careful there, son!</i>  I am not sure how many hitpoints your 59th level pet has, but our best pets appear to have about 2750 hitpoints and hit for 60 max.</P><P>Although there are some <i>Magicians</i> who advocate having much stronger pets post-50 and especially post-55, the general consensus appears to be the real issue is ATK.  That is, the problem is that our pets are not hitting the big mobs.</P><P>One popular proposal involves adding an ATK bonus to <i>Burnout</i>, our pet buff line.  As I see your pets' eyes gleam with madness, I assume you have something of the kind.</P><P>Would not an increase in ATK be mostly sufficient to address your concerns about pets?  If not, why not?  In any case, as a <i>Magician</i> I am forced to be dubious about a <i>Necromancer</i> pet that would appear to out-tank <i>Greater Vocaration Earth</i>.</P><P>I also saw this in another thread:<BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>. So now, name me a mob where any necro can outdamage a wiz in a long fight ? Answer is NO. NONE. We were NEVER the masters of long fights, we were juz allowed our dots to run its full course of damage for those and dats about it. This is not a rent, this is what I observed so far, its a fact that we necros need to recognize and stop decieving ourselves.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote>and it resonated with something I observed earlier, only going the other way around.  That is, it seems to me, ignorant <i>Mage</i> that I am, that if <i>Necromancers</i> are to be the <i>Masters of Long Term Damage</i>, then what is required are long but powerful DoTs <i>(assuming that stacking is resolved)</i>.  Otherwise, in long fights, a DoT is not much distinguishable from a nuke, especially if they ever stack.</P><P>It seems to me a valid question.  Supposing that DoTs eventually stack, how can they be fairly distinguished from direct damage spells without either nerfing them or making them overpowered.</P><P>Respectfully,</P><P><BR>Razamatazz Pizzazz<BR>Mage of a Thousand Words<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
